---
description: Error handling conventions
globs: "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use rich for user-facing error messages
- Include descriptive error messages with actionable information
- Log detailed error information when verbose mode is enabled
- For external API errors (e.g., LLM API calls), implement appropriate retries
- For CLI commands, return appropriate exit codes on failure
- Validate user inputs early to provide clear validation errors
